+{"id":"frankenredis-omff","title":"rv89 part 4a: OBJECT ENCODING listpack_ex/hashtable_ex + keyspace events + DEBUG OBJECT expired_fields","description":"Narrowed slice of br-frankenredis-3jrv. No RDB / AOF / HGETEX-HGETDEL yet — those are part 4b (RDB) and part 4c (AOF + HGETEX/HGETDEL).\n\nScope:\n- fr-store::object_encoding: when a hash carries at least one per-field TTL, report 'listpack_ex' / 'hashtable_ex' instead of 'listpack' / 'hashtable'.\n- Keyspace events: emit 'hexpire', 'hpexpire', 'hexpireat', 'hpexpireat', 'hpersist', 'hexpired' on the right commands / lazy-reaps.\n- DEBUG OBJECT reports an 'expired_fields' counter equal to the Store's stat_expired_keys-derived delta for the given key.\n- Tests per axis.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-23T23:14:51.577273514Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-23T23:17:08.712977320Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T23:17:08.711013313Z","close_reason":"Landed in f462d78: OBJECT ENCODING flips listpack/hashtable → listpack_ex/hashtable_ex when any per-field TTL is present; hexpired keyspace event fires on both bulk and targeted lazy reaps. 2 new tests; fr-store 280/0. Command-side keyspace events (HEXPIRE → hexpire etc.) and DEBUG OBJECT expired_fields deferred to a future bead alongside RDB + AOF (3jrv remains open).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
